# Project Title
Cryptex

The Cryptex project was made for both developers and users.

For Developers, it was made for them to hash(with an algoritm), or 
encrypt(with a key of their choice) their software or file, so that 
the integrity of the file or software can be checked by their users.

Cryptex was made for developers to show and prove the integrity
of their software or file. 

Cryptex has a data integrity verification made for the developers 
and users to prove and verify their file integrity.

Cryptex has other uses, it can be used to transfer information 
between variuos people so it does not leak to unwanted audience.

Cryptex can also be used to transfer files. if an encrypted file 
is given from a user to another, as long at the other user has the
key, they can get the original file back.

## Live Demo
It is available on github the repo name is cryptograph.

## Tech Stack
* **Frontend:** HTML, Tailwind CSS, JavaScript
* **Backend:** Node.js, Express

## Getting Started
This website was made intoo three sectors and they are: 

1. the hashing sector.
2. the verification sector.
3. the cipher sector.

THE HASHING SECTOR: This sector uses algoirthms(SHA-256, SHA-1, MD5) 
 to convert your text or file into unreadable 
 text so the integrity of the file or text 
 still remains, and can be checked if altered,
 and that's where the verification sector comes in.

THE VERIFICATION SECTOR: This sector checks the
  integrity of a file or text using it's hash that 
  was generated by the first hahsing section, or by 
  abother hashing website(as long as the algorithm are same).
  it takes in the file or text, you paste the hash of the 
  file or text, and it checks if the file has been altered.

THE CIPHER SECTOR: Unlike other sectors, this sector does not
 hash your file or text, rather it turns your file or text
 into an unreadable cipher text, thereby encrypting it and
 the text or file can be converted back to it's original form
 thereby decrypting it. it uses industry standard encryption
  AES-GCM to encrypt the given file or text, and was built 
  in a way to encrypt your data to the extent a hacker 
  cannot use a rainbow table to get the encrypted data.


